  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And Abraham gave all that he had unto Isaac. By his last will and testament; not all out of his own hand, while he lived, at least he reserved somewhat for himself, and for gifts to his other children; so his servant declared to the parents and friends of Rebekah, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 24:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; wherefore some render the words here \"had given\" (d); or the sense is, that he had at that time purposed and promised to give all that he had to Isaac, and now he actually did it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(d) \"dederat\", Junius & Tremellius, Piscator. ",
